# TrustPass AI — Google Cloud Guidance

For your hackathon build, don’t overcomplicate it with too many enterprise services. Build a **clean Google Cloud MVP** with **7 AI agents**, Firebase, Gemini, Cloud Run, Firestore, Cloud Storage, and optional Document AI.

The goal is:

```text
Upload evidence → AI autofills profile → User confirms → AI verifies → Admin approves → Passport issued → Linkages recommended
```

---

# 1. Recommended Google Cloud Architecture

## MVP Architecture

```text
Next.js Frontend
      ↓
Firebase Auth
      ↓
Cloud Run Backend API
      ↓
Gemini / Vertex AI
      ↓
Firestore
      ↓
Cloud Storage
      ↓
Passport / Stamp / Linkage Records
```

## Google Cloud Services You Should Use

| Service                           | Use in TrustPass AI                                                                                                                                                                                                                          |
| --------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Firebase Authentication**       | Login, signup, Google login, role-based access. Firebase Auth supports email/password, phone, and federated identity providers like Google. ([Firebase][1])                                                                                  |
| **Cloud Firestore**               | Store users, startups, mentors, passports, stamps, verification results, linkages, and admin decisions. Firestore is a cloud-hosted NoSQL document database accessible from web and backend SDKs. ([Firebase][2])                            |
| **Cloud Storage**                 | Store uploaded pitch decks, CVs, registration docs, evidence files, and generated passport PDFs/images. Cloud Storage is Google Cloud’s managed object storage for unstructured data. ([Google Cloud][3])                                    |
| **Cloud Run**                     | Host your backend APIs and agent workflows.                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| **Gemini API / Vertex AI Gemini** | AI extraction, autofill, verification, scoring, explanation, and linkage reasoning. Gemini supports function calling/tool use, which lets models call external functions/APIs and return structured actions. ([Google AI for Developers][4]) |
| **Document AI**                   | Optional, for better document extraction from PDFs and scanned documents. Document AI converts unstructured document data into structured data. ([Google Cloud Documentation][5])                                                            |
| **Secret Manager**                | Store API keys and service credentials safely.                                                                                                                                                                                               |
| **Cloud Logging**                 | Debug backend, AI calls, verification errors, and audit issues.                                                                                                                                                                              |

For the hackathon, you can skip complex enterprise setup like BigQuery, advanced Vertex AI Agent Builder, Kubernetes, or full workflow orchestration.

